The man accidentally shot by US Vice President Dick Cheney while hunting in Texas is in stable condition at Christus Spohn Hospital Memorial in Corpus Christi.
The prominent Texas lawyer, Harry Whittington, suffered injuries to his shoulder, upper body, chest, and neck.
Cheney's delayed notification of the incident sparked criticism, with questions raised about the handling of the situation.
Despite the mishap, Whittington remained in good health and was reported to be cracking jokes while baffled by the media attention.
The incident highlighted the importance of safety and awareness during hunting activities.
